TASK_TYPE=feature
TASK_DESCRIPTION=Tasks must be the single source of truth for everything that happened during execution. This is a two-part feature:

STORAGE — Each task becomes a directory: .doey/tasks/<ID>/
  - task.meta (the current .task metadata: id, title, status, type, tags, timestamps)
  - plan.md (implementation plan produced by manager)
  - hypotheses.md (hypotheses with confidence levels, outcomes)
  - reports/ (research reports, audit results)
  - messages/ (SM<->worker, manager<->worker comms captured during task)
  - files-changed.log (list of files edited/created during task, with pane/worker attribution)
  - attachments/ (arbitrary output artifacts — screenshots, logs, JSON results)
  - decisions.md (key decisions and rationale logged during execution)
  - notes.md (free-form notes)
  
The .task file in the root stays as a lightweight index/pointer. Stop hooks, manager validation, and worker output flows must write to the appropriate location in this directory structure. Migrate existing .task files gracefully (create dir, move metadata).

TUI — In the Go TUI Tasks tab, selecting a task opens a rich detail view with tabbed/sectioned layout:
  - Overview: status, type, tags, created/updated timestamps
  - Plan: rendered plan.md content
  - Hypotheses: hypothesis list with confidence + outcomes
  - Reports: list of reports, select to view content
  - Messages: chronological message log from task execution
  - Files Changed: list of files touched, with worker attribution
  - Attachments: arbitrary artifacts, viewable
  - Decisions & Notes: decisions.md + notes.md content

All sections must scroll correctly. Handle empty sections gracefully (show placeholder text). Navigation between sections via tab keys or left/right. This is the primary way users understand what happened during a task.

